Navy ships, fishermen and search and rescue teams have found more than 200 survivors since the ferry sank late with some 600 people on board.
The Senopati Nusantara sank quickly after being pounded by heavy waves for more than 10 hours as it neared the end of a two-day journey from the Indonesian section of Borneo island to the country's main island of Java.
Officials say bad weather was the cause of the accident.
an air force plane dropped food and water to some survivors stranded in the Java Sea.
